Algebra 1 Tutor — Licensing
===========================

This project is licensed in two parts, plus a note on images:

- CODE AND BUILD TOOLING is under the MIT License (full text below). This covers
  the Python in `_verification/` (the build, generation, and verification
  scripts and their tests), `curriculum.yaml`, `requirements.txt`, the CI
  config in `.circleci/`, and `.gitattributes`.

- COURSE CONTENT is under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0
  International License (CC BY-NC 4.0), described in `LICENSE-CONTENT`. This
  covers the Agent Skill and its lessons (`algebra-1-tutor/`), the
  student-facing prose (`textbook-src/`), and the generated website (the HTML
  and CSS under `docs/`).

- AI-GENERATED IMAGES in `docs/assets/*.jpg` are released as CC0 1.0 (public
  domain dedication). See `docs/assets/README.md`.

Third-party materials (OpenStax, the Common Core State Standards, and the cited
research) are referenced for further reading only; none of their text is
reproduced or adapted here. See `algebra-1-tutor/references/sources.md`.

